The paper proposes a new distributed learning paradigm called federated learning to tackle privacy issues in distributed learning. It specifically focuses on the problem of anomaly detection, which can be considered as a special classification problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DB (Databases).
